==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Syllabus
<hw>Syl"la*bus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Syllabuses</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Syllabi</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., fr. the same source as E.
<ets>syllable</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A compendium containing the
heads of a discourse, and the like; an abstract.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The headnote of a reported case;
the brief statement of the points of law determined prefixed to a
reported case. The opinion controls the syllabus, the latter being
merely explanatory of the former.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Syllepsis</ent>⟦br⟧
